  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study aims to evaluate:

        -  the frequency of subsyndromal symptoms or disorders observed during interepisode phases
           in bipolar patients, particularly after a depressive episode in which these subsyndromal
           disorders are the most frequent

        -  the functional impact of these disorders, factors or symptom thresholds associated with
           functional remission, and factors associated with symptomatic remission over a
           sufficient follow-up (12 months).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Evaluation of sub-syndromal symptoms after acute depressive episode in bipolar disorder
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
